                  UNDOCUMENTED CHANGES<br />
<br />
Resistance changed in pvp!!!!!!!!!!!<br />
<br />
Sleep /freeze/slow land 10-30% now from almost 0-10% (depending on the other person's gear)It is still insufficient as we only depend on those for survivability but ..... we shall see in gu5<br />
<br />
Seradon falling star finally lands (4/5 attempts).<br />
<br />
All droppable spells are now trainable on all npc trainers (no need to spend hours on end for superior chaos volley) (guildies confirmed this... i have all droppable spells and cannot verify myself)<br />
<br />
Superior chaos volley is a KILLER!!! (both for the caster and the receiver)<br />
<br />
We kill fast now in pvp and die even faster!!!!<br />
<br />
We seem to be doing a lot more crticals in pvp if you are full critical gear that is. Criticals now rarely miss. (that applies to all classes)<br />
<br />
Most droppable/lootable/questable gear has had a significant boost in their attributes and their AC compared to all t5 gear. Some had an enormous boost.<br />
<br />
<br />
Bards can no longer casr ANY song while they are on a flying mount. Invisibility issues in parties where player lost sight of the other invisible players (had to stop for 4 seconds till he saw the other players around) has been slightly fixed depending on the number of players around and connection or server lag.... still a vast improvement.<br />
<br />
Bards dying and releasing to altar no longer have to wait more than 30 seconds beofre they can sing again.<br />
<br />
Lots of areas are now inaccessible to players flying over them on a flying mount.... you get dismounted...<br />
<br />
Warriors/DKs/Paladins are even more gimped now to spells.... <br />
<br />
Necros are next to impossible to kill in duel (unless you jump on them)<br />
<br />
Mobs drop special items that have no stats on them but can be deconstructed for crystals or expendables (orbs etc etc)<br />
<br />
Aggro loss in pvp after running 50m away from player has still not been fixed. You lose aggro only after your dinner is ready and served.<br />
<br />
UNDOCUMENTED EMOTICONS ($%^^$^%$^$%^^%$%$%^$^ designed those helmets?) (Awesome warrior helmets.... think we laughed for hours on end when those dwarves and rakis can showing off their TAAAALLLLL helmets)<br />
