not sure, only new spell i got was Stop XP gain, and i am still missing Chromatic Halo<br />
<br />
As for the changes, after pvping all day vs different classes, i can say that Sigil has totally overpowered druids<br />
<br />
I really dont understand why they do that?? It is a bad habit they got when they make one class totally out of line. Anyway, to say it short, druid was insta killing me from the altar as i was camping him there. He would regen to half life, then cast deadly swarms and I was dead in less then one sec, no time to even throw a char at him<br />
<br />
I was pvping several druids, and ALL of them were dropping me in maximum of 3-5 sec. Needless to say, i have 7 pieces of APW gear, and at times break 3k or 4k infamy.<br />
<br />
Just a summary of what druids can do besides dropping us in one spell (deadly swarm)<br />
<br />
They have around 12 or 15 sec DA, another DA Treeform that last for a long time as well. And during their DA they have 3 elemental pet that each hit for about 200-300, and run faster then my mount speed (happened several times, usually they run fast, but i was shocked when they caught up with my 315% mount speed)<br />
<br />
Anyway, i still think sorcs are fun to play, but now we have another 1 shot class. the other were monks, which would one shot me almost every time. Their shurikens hit for 1800, and have 40 range as well. And i am not even talking about their leaps, and now they have in GU4 Feigh Death that works in PVP, and it insta mezzes you.<br />
<br />
Roots and Snares dont land at all really, i as lucky in the beginning, but after PVPing all night i have to stay they still get resissted about 95%. I am thinking of taking them out from my hotbars period. And that a class defying ability!!<br />
<br />
Seradon DOES land MUCH more often, up from 0% to about 20-25%. THanks for that at least ))<br />
<br />
Also, in GU4 they have broker out mirror, nullifying and CHromatic BArrier wards!!! Please, FIX IT ASAP, those spells are worthless now.<br />
<br />
THen, our force barrier seems to work with about 30-40% of different abilities from other classes. Monks NEVER get hit by even a ministun, rogues get hit maybe 30% of the time, but thats after they dropped your health to 10% and your are dying to evisirate anyway.<br />
<br />
Force barrier is my most often used spell, because sometimes it cancels out dots that shamans or necros throw at you. BUt now in GU4 they have seem to fix that ((<br />
<br />
Guys, now i am out of ALL our defense abilities, making sorcs INCREDIBLY fragile. I mean, most classes can range shot use with spears/shurikens/arrows/daggers etc in 3-5 secs. (i am only talking about 50s pvp)<br />
<br />
<br />
Just a small summary: <br />
<br />
1. sorcs get hit for damage cap almost ALL the time, (about 30% of health or so, or even more), <br />
<br />
2. with macros we get ONE shooted ALOT (now there are even more macro classes since in GU4 melees can combine melee and spell abilities in one macro making it insta, for example, dreadknights)<br />
<br />
3. Our class defying abilities get resisted every time (root, snare, mez and seradon a little less)<br />
<br />
4. Force Crit and force 50% damage recast timer is WAY too High, other classes have force crit on like a 1min refresh times, let alone that RAhz Incur legendary Helm that gives 3sec of CRit!!!! that makes melee so overpowered in PVP!!!!!, and out RAhz Helm is WORTHLESS, I HAVE NEVER RAN OOM IN more than a few months now, mana is simply not an issue for sorcs)<br />
<br />
5. MIrror, nullifying, disperce, reflect, disenchant does NOT work in PVP   /cry<br />
<br />
