		<div id="post_message_1309541">
                  
                  forget is almost as good as nothing IF and only IF now with the changes to tank classes using the 2 handers , the tanks do proper damage and criticals (no too excessive) and the classes who can feed aggro on him also do the job right. The aggro swtich from one tank to another is also another factor to be noted, becuase if tank a has aggro and tank b gains aggro after sometime it seems the bosses wipe out all aggro on tank A. So you have to wait on damage once more till the main tank regains full aggro.<br />
<br />
I cannot really say which forget is better than the other in terms of numbers and parsers but i RARELY to NEVER got aggro on mobs if i waited enough on my damage at the beginning and if i ever did when main tank died or another tank took aggro the new forget worked sufficiently to remove aggro from me.<br />
<br />
Forget is not the best cure to lose aggro. Coordination with the main tank and aggro feeders is.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
